  "text": "We conducted Chi square test to examine the association between financial inclusion programmes and women empowerment where financial inclusion variables act as independent variables and women's economic empowerment variables, as mentioned above, are dependent variables. Findings are provided in Table 11 . According to Table 11 , there is significant association between the variables. As the level of significance of the computed value is less than 0.05(5% level of significance), so the alternative hypothesis that there is an association between financial inclusion and women's economic empowerment is accepted. Our findings are similar to the findings of [CITATION_1] and [CITATION_2] . Thus we conclude that financial inclusion promotes women empowerment in developing economies, like Bangladesh. ",
